HEADWORD: Larker
<hw>Lark"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 3d <er>Lark</er>,
for sense 1, and 1st <er>Lark</er>, for sense 2.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A catcher of larks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who indulges in a lark or frolic.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lark's-heel</ent>⟦br⟧
